 FormFactor, Inc. 
Livermore, CA 
 We live in a mobile driven world where technology is constantly improving. Semiconductor manufacturers need a partner as they pioneer and drive the most advanced integrated circuits (ICs) ever made. FormFactor is the worldâ€™s leading supplier of semiconductor test and measurement products used to test the ICs that power the majority of smart phones and tablets on the planet, as well as electronic systems used in computing, consumer, automotive, Artificial Intelligence (AI) and other applications. We are a big company with a small time feel. Working at FormFactor gives you the opportunity to work with cutting edge technology, have a direct influence on next generation products hitting the market and drive the overall growth and development of the semiconductor industry. 
 We are a fast-paced, agile, growing company that values diversity of thought and constantly strives for a more diverse, inclusive environment. We are looking for enthusiastic, talented individuals who can thrive in a changing and challenging environment. 
 
 PURPOSE 
 The MEMS development engineer will work in our world-class MEMS wafer fabrication facility and interface with various process modules to develop new process. This position is responsible for the new process development and the next generation spring development 
 
 ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES 
 Develop next generation MEMS products and new process development and process transfer to HVM. 
 Explore new process, new material and innovative process capability for next generation MEMS spring invention. 
 
 EDUCATION, EXPERIENCE AND SKILLS REQUIRED 
 MS + 8 years or PhD +5 years in MEMS, Mechanical Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Material Science or a related Engineering fields. 
 A minimum of 5 years of MEMS process integration, program management, and MEMS process development and transfer, with a proven record of problem solving and releasing manufacturing processes to high-volume capability. 
 Expert knowledge of MEMS process integration and the interaction of process, design, materials, and reliability. 
 Direct experience in one or more of the following module areas: Lithography, Thin Films, Etch, Plating and Planarization. 
 Experience in semiconductor or MEMS research/development and manufacturing environments. 
 Strong communication, data analysis, and design of experiment skills are required. 
 Ability to demonstrate the use of FMEA, Root-cause Analysis (RCA), SPC, DOE, and data analysis. Matlab, JMP, AutoCAD, MS Excel experience preferred. 
 Finite element simulation and design experience with SolidWorks & Ansys is a plus. 
 Experience with structured problem solving tools such as 8D 
 
